<p>
<span class="red_intro">D</span>aniel Kraken had Merlot Bot smashed to bits in his mansion in the middle of the night. His jagged corpse clinked in his silk sheets as it was carried downstairs, staining the stairs an appropriately human red. His vineyards burned until dawn, every trellis was reduced to stamped ash by Daniel’s secret police.
</p>
<p>
For all Daniel knew, Merlot Bot had lead the Butterfly Boar to Kraken HQ when he had mapped out the route of acorn feeders. If he could let a White Wine Automaton survive for centuries, if he could risk their entire operation out of some sniveling sentimentality, then he had to be excised from the enterprise.
</p>
<p>
At least Champagne Bot was dead. That guy was arrogant as all get out. But now Fawn, her smug little page, AND Comet had escaped assassination and could undermine his entire empire if they blabbed about either his alien provenance or his role in introducing both the highs and lows of progress to an island that, before his arrival, could have been characterized as an idyllic, loving paradise without need or want.
</p>
