  The butterfly boar was tearing across an open field, straight towards Kraken HQ,
  with Comet standing astride his bristly back, holding the chrysalis’s chains in her hands like reins,
  her unribboned hair blowing in the freely in the wind from the gathering storm. Fawn and her page were kneeling down,
  each one gripping one of Comet’s legs. Fawn was licking down the fuzz on the heads of the island’s last two tiger cubs, who mewled in bindle in the crook of her arms. The boar’s chrysalis flopped
  along the ground behind them, spent of whatever fresh apocalypse had been growing inside of it. Small Almighty's ozone B.O. caused the nanohairs in Daniel's
  false nostrils to stand on end as the teenaged bolt streaked out of the dark sky behind him.
  Daniel looked out over the world he had created, and for the first time in his life, he wept during the day.
</p>
